isInputFileDirectory

public boolean isInputFileDirectory()
Returns true if the input from the user should be directory and returns false if the input from the user should be a file. Note that in Java, a File object can represent a directory or a file. When importing from Balsamiq Mockups, a directory consisting of all of the .bmml files must be given.

Specified by:
isInputFileDirectory in class edu.cmu.cs.hcii.cogtool.model.ImportConverter
Returns:
the boolean value of weather the inputFile should be a file or directory

allowedExtensions

public java.lang.String[] allowedExtensions()
Returns a String array consisting of all of the valid extensions to be imported using this converter file. The allowedExtensions method is used whether a file or a directory is given as input Balsamiq Mockups files are saved as a .bmml file or a .xml file No problem will occur if a specified extension is duplicated in the array.
